      In the **Frostfang Peaks**, where the gods once feasted before abandoning mortals to the cold, stood the **Storm-Hall of Veyra**, a refuge for those caught in the endless blizzards. Its rule was carved into the doorframe: *‘No guest leaves without bread, no guest is turned from the fire—lest the hearth’s embers choke the living, and the mountain swallow the hall whole.’* For generations, the keepers of the hall honored this, even when the larder ran bare.

