      At dawn, Hrold found the figure at the **Edge of the World**, where the mountain drops into the abyss. ‘You broke the law,’ Hrold said. ‘The loaf was given. You did not take it.’ The stranger turned, their hood falling back to reveal a face **stitched together from frozen corpses**—a **winter-wraith**, one of the **Unfed Dead**, bound to the world by hunger. ‘I could not eat,’ it whispered. ‘I am already starving.’ Hrold did not hesitate. He took the **last crust** from his belt and pressed it into the wraith’s hands. ‘Then you will eat now,’ he commanded.

